      • application

        public static BuiltApplication application(android.content.Context context,
                                           java.lang.String apiKey)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Authenticates the application api key of your application. This must be called before your application uses Built.io Backend sdk.
        You can find your application key from web.
        Parameters:
        context - application context.
        apiKey - application api Key of your application on Built.io Backend.
        Returns:
        BuiltApplication instance.

        Example :
         //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltApplication builtApplication = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
